HEADWORD: Hogget
<hw>Hog"get</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See Hog, and
<er>Hoggerel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A young boar of the second
year.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sheep or colt alter it has passed its first
year.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hogging</ent>⟦br⟧
